WEBVTT

00:00:00.280 --> 00:00:02.540
Welcome to this section on machine learning.

00:00:02.540 --> 00:00:04.200
So machine learning is not something you need to know

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:06.590
in-depth for the exam but there are a few

00:00:06.590 --> 00:00:09.400
certification services that you need to know.

00:00:09.400 --> 00:00:12.090
So the first one is Amazon Rekognition,

00:00:12.090 --> 00:00:14.980
and as the name indicates, it's used to recognize objects,

00:00:14.980 --> 00:00:18.450
people, text and scene in images and videos

00:00:18.450 --> 00:00:19.730
using machine learning.

00:00:19.730 --> 00:00:21.920
So you can do facial analysis and facial search

00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:24.270
to do user verification and count people.

00:00:24.270 --> 00:00:27.160
And with this, we can create a database of familiar faces

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:29.410
or compare against celebrities.

00:00:29.410 --> 00:00:31.830
The use cases for Rekognition would be labeling,

00:00:31.830 --> 00:00:34.240
content moderation, text detection,

00:00:34.240 --> 00:00:36.210
face detection and analysis,

00:00:36.210 --> 00:00:39.090
for example the gender, the age range and the emotions,

00:00:39.090 --> 00:00:42.360
face search and verification, celebrity recognition,

00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:44.090
and finally, pathing.

00:00:44.090 --> 00:00:46.460
So if you wanna learn more, you can check out their website

00:00:46.460 --> 00:00:47.890
which I think is very helpful.

00:00:47.890 --> 00:00:49.340
So on the Rekognition websites,

00:00:49.340 --> 00:00:51.900
we can we can automate our image and video analysis

00:00:51.900 --> 00:00:52.950
with machine learning.

00:00:52.950 --> 00:00:53.940
And I really like this website

00:00:53.940 --> 00:00:55.590
because it shows you how it works.

00:00:55.590 --> 00:00:57.040
So for example, for this image,

00:00:57.040 --> 00:00:59.130
we can identify the elements of this image,

00:00:59.130 --> 00:01:01.570
for example, a person, a rock and mountain bike,

00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:03.120
a crest and outdoors.

00:01:03.120 --> 00:01:05.490
We can label, for example, what we see in the images,

00:01:05.490 --> 00:01:07.740
for example, Golden Retrievers or dogs.

00:01:07.740 --> 00:01:10.150
Then I can look at content moderation

00:01:10.150 --> 00:01:13.030
to make sure that it's appropriate for all ages.

00:01:13.030 --> 00:01:15.340
I can detect text, for example for a run,

00:01:15.340 --> 00:01:18.480
we want to see the numbers of each runner in the run.

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:20.130
We can do face detection and analysis.

00:01:20.130 --> 00:01:22.840
For example, this person looks happy, she is smiling,

00:01:22.840 --> 00:01:24.850
her eyes are open and she's a female.

00:01:24.850 --> 00:01:26.240
Face search and verification,

00:01:26.240 --> 00:01:28.770
maybe if you have a security application.

00:01:28.770 --> 00:01:30.880
Finally, if you want to recognize a celebrity,

00:01:30.880 --> 00:01:32.280
you can take a picture of them,

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:34.970
and this is the CTO of AWS.

00:01:34.970 --> 00:01:36.400
And then finally, pathing.

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:39.060
For example, if you're monitoring a soccer game,

00:01:39.060 --> 00:01:41.080
you could see where everyone is going to do

00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:43.040
maybe some real time analytics.

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:45.080
So Rekognition is just a service you need to know

00:01:45.080 --> 00:01:46.550
at a high level for the exam

00:01:46.550 --> 00:01:47.383
but I really like this page

00:01:47.383 --> 00:01:49.430
because it demonstrate the use cases.

00:01:49.430 --> 00:01:51.180
I will see you in the next lecture.